-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Aug 14
-- 
-- Thu Aug 14, 2014 02:35AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Aug 14 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Interim Prime Minister Georgi Bliznashki sent a letter to the leader of European Socialists Sergei Stanishev urging him to back the candidacy of Bulgarian Kristalina Georgieva for EU foreign policy chief in the European Commission. (24 Chasa, Standart) CAPITAL DAILY - Bulgaria's third largest lender First Investment Bank <5F4.BB> has to prepare a restructuring plan by the end of August as part of the conditions under which the European Commission allowed the finance ministry to prop up the bank's liquidity at the end of June.  24 CHASA - Sofia airport has installed a special temperature scanner aimed tat establishing passengers with high fever and protect against spreading of the deadly Ebola virus disease. (24 Chasa) -- A Bulgarian court will rule on 12 appeals against the regional development ministry permit which allowed the construction of South Stream gas pipeline project. (Sega, Capital Daily, Trud)